Currently all you get is something like the below:

{code}
10.20.4.101 749x1726305x1 Gene.Gray [23/Jul/2014:12:29:20 +1000] "POST /servicedesk/customer/portal/2/create/11 HTTP/1.1" 400 162 185 "https://jira.example:8443/servicedesk/customer/portal/2/create/11" "Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 6.1; rv:30.0) Gecko/20100101 Firefox/30.0" "1jtua6f"
{code}

This shows a HTTP 400, however not why it failed. Something such as [Chrome Developer Tools|https://developers.google.com/chrome-developer-tools/docs/overview#access] is required to identify the {{reasonCode}} in the HTTP response.

In this example, {{cv.request.create.workflow.failure}} was caused by an improperly configured post-function in the Create Issue transition.

